text: Maharaja Ala Singh (1691–1765) or Baba Ala Singh was the first Maharaja of the historical princely state of Patiala. He was born into a Jat Sidhu sikh family. Previously he was Jathedar of Phulkian Misl. He was born in 1691 at Phul, in present-day Bathinda district of the Punjab. == References == == Further reading == * Category:1691 births Category:1765 deaths Category:People from Patiala Category:Punjabi people
